HEADWORD: Melitose
<hw>Mel"i*tose`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>me`li</grk> honey.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A variety of
sugar isomeric with sucrose, extracted from cotton seeds and from the
so-called Australian manna (a secretion of certain species of
Eucalyptus).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

